# Remove Linked List Elements (LeetCode 203)

## Problem Statement
Remove all the nodes of a linked list that have `Node.val == val`, and return the new head.

---

## Approach
- Use a **dummy node** pointing to head (handles edge cases easily).
- Traverse list with a pointer.
- Skip nodes with matching value, otherwise move forward.

---

## Code (C++)

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    ListNode* removeElements(ListNode* head, int val) {
        ListNode* temp = new ListNode(0);
        temp->next = head;
        ListNode* curr = temp;
        
        while (curr->next != NULL) {
            if (curr->next->val == val) {
                curr->next = curr->next->next;
            } else {
                curr = curr->next;
            }
        }
        return temp->next;
    }
};
